Endpoint deleted August 2021; Please use '/chat/v4/blocked'.

**Response:** named requests root object: a flat list of friend request property groups with 'pid' and 'name' inside (could have zero or more entries):

```
{
  "requests": [
    {
      "name":         "[friend name]",
      "note":         "[friend note]",     // Can be set to contain information about the friend request. (ex. recofriender saves the player name from social media here)
      "pid":          "[friend pid]",
      "subscription": "pending_out"        //either "pending_out" or "pending_in" (sent or received request)
    }
  ]
}
```


Endpoint deleted July 2021; Please use '/chat/v6/friendrequests'.

**Response:** named friends root object: a flat list of friend property groups with 'pid' and 'name' inside (could have zero or more entries):```
{
  "friends": [
    {
      "displayGroup": "[display group name]",   // The current display group of this friend. This will either be the regular group or a meta group (ex. "MOBILE", "OFFLINE")
      "group":        "[group name]",           // The group this friend is a part of
      "name":         "[friend name]",
      "note":         "[friend note]",
      "pid":          "[friend pid]",
      "priority":     "[group priority value]"
    }
    ...
  ]
}
```


Endpoint deleted August 2021; Please use '/chat/v4/friends'.

**Response:** named groups root object: an ordered list of friend groups. First is highest displayed.  Could have one or more entries, always has a default group:

```
{
  "groups": [
    {
      "collapsed":    [collapsed],                  // If the group is open or closed
      "isMetaGroup":  [isMetaGroup],                // If the group is a meta group (ex. "MOBILE", "OFFLINE")
      "name":        "[group name]"
    }
    ...
  ]
}
```

**Mobile and Offline Groups**

The mobile and offline groups will appear in the list of groups if the "chatGroupMobile" or "chatGroupOffline" settings are set to true. They will appear like this:

```
{
  "groups": [
    ...
    {
      "collapsed": [collapsed],
      "isMetaGroup": true,
      "name": "MOBILE"
    },
    ...
    {
      "collapsed": [collapsed],
      "isMetaGroup": true,
      "name": "OFFLINE"
    }
    ...
  ]
}
```

Friends who are either in the "offline" or "mobile" state will automatically be given the corresponding "displayGroup" (ex. either "OFFLINE" or "MOBILE") in place of their regular group name. If the settings are turned off the groups will be removed and the friends' "displayGroup"s will be set back to their regular group names.


